hoe /həʊ/

(hoeing,hoed,hoes) 

1. N-COUNT A hoe is a gardening tool with a long handle and a small square blade, which you use to remove small weeds and break up the surface of the soil. 锄头 

2. V-T If you hoe a field or crop, you use a hoe on the weeds or soil there. 锄 (以除杂草或松土) 

例： I have to feed the chickens and hoe the potatoes. 我必须喂鸡，还得给土豆除草松土。

